# Privacy policy

Last updated: January 10, 2025

## Introduction

We take your privacy seriously. This policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal data when you use Vokabulo.

## Data collection

### Information you provide

We collect information you provide directly to us when using our services, including:
- Account information (email, name)
- Language learning data (vocabulary lists, study progress)
- Settings and preferences

### Automatically collected information

When you use Vokabulo, we automatically collect:
- Usage data (features used, time spent)
- Device information (browser type, operating system)
- Log data (IP address, access times)

## How we use your data

We use your data to:
- Provide and improve our services
- Personalize your learning experience
- Send important service updates
- Analyze usage patterns to enhance features
- Ensure security and prevent fraud

## Data storage and security

Your data is stored securely using industry-standard encryption. We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information against unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction.

## Your rights

You have the right to:
- Access your personal data
- Correct inaccurate information
- Request deletion of your data
- Export your data
- Opt-out of marketing communications

## Third-party services

We may use third-party services for analytics and infrastructure. These services have their own privacy policies and are required to protect your data.

## Changes to this policy

We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the new policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.

## Contact

If you have questions about this privacy policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at the email address provided in our legal notice.
